qca-ppe: bump to 3041090e to build against current main phylink

OpenWrt PR #22381 pins qca-ppe at acf30c0f (2026-05-16), which still uses the
old phylink available_pcs field. OpenWrt main's phylink PCS patches moved to a
new PCS OP, so merging the PR onto latest main fails to build qca_ppe_main.c
(struct phylink_config has no member named available_pcs).

The next qca-ppe commit, 3041090e (2026-05-17) "update available_pcs handling
with new PCS OP", is the fix. Bump to it until PR #22381 updates its own pin
(then drop this patch). PKG_MIRROR_HASH is skipped since we track a moving
upstream and do not vendor the tarball hash.

diff --git a/package/kernel/qca-ppe/Makefile b/package/kernel/qca-ppe/Makefile
index 488abc6..38176b1 100644
--- a/package/kernel/qca-ppe/Makefile
+++ b/package/kernel/qca-ppe/Makefile
@@ -5,9 +5,9 @@ PKG_RELEASE:=1
 
 PKG_SOURCE_URL:=https://github.com/openwrt/qca-ppe.git
 PKG_SOURCE_PROTO:=git
-PKG_SOURCE_DATE:=2026-05-16
-PKG_SOURCE_VERSION:=acf30c0fcb04a240d427a26c5efad55622a61652
-PKG_MIRROR_HASH:=33e937cdaa5fec260a7dc9b46be21825f3f18004b660a34daa7003e1f4bedca5
+PKG_SOURCE_DATE:=2026-05-17
+PKG_SOURCE_VERSION:=3041090e0aa1a4d77c7e8c61aba99e5ead7b3b37
+PKG_MIRROR_HASH:=skip
 
 PKG_BUILD_PARALLEL:=1
 PKG_FLAGS:=nonshared
